$interpreted: Tica: Hmph! Behold my power!
Tica: Atlas Marionette Workshop VI, hehe~ I smell an important clue hiding inside!
Tica: Yikes... this silence is getting on my nerves. As I expected, this workshop is creepy, just like every other workshop.
Tica: Ooh, more documents. Lemme take a look...

Tica: In addition to crafting marionettes that commemorate deceased relatives, 

our workshop also crafts performance marionettes that operate via runes carved into them...
Tica: These are design blueprints for the performance marionettes. Let's see...
Tica: So the ones with runes carved into them are for performance purposes, while the ones that don't have runes are to commemorate family members.

Tica: Huh? How strange; according to the blueprints, the performance marionettes can only act out simple commands like singing or dancing.
Doesn't say anything about attacking people though?
Tica: So the dolls' weird movement...can safely say it has something to do with the singing and that weird runic glow?
Tica: T-That's really frightening...
Tica: No, I'm not scared. You're scared!
Tica: Hmm, what is that?
Tica: Origin of the Atlas Marionette Religion, Volume 1...
Tica: The wandering boy Karl came across a performance marionette.
Tica: Whenever Karl felt depressed and tired from wandering the streets, the marionette would sing a beautiful song to comfort Karl.
Tica: Karl's mother often sang him the same song when she was still alive. Thus, Karl always said to others that...
Tica: ...the marionette contains his mother's soul.
Tica: OUCH!
Tica: T-They're here as well!?
Tica: Now that you've learned your lesson; don't you dare sneak up behind me again!
Tica: Origin of the Atlas Marionette Religion, Volume 2...
Tica: ...Until the day Karl died, the marionette never stopped singing. Her voice sounded as if she was sobbing.
Tica: The people of Atlas believed that the marionette did indeed contain the soul of Karl's mother. Therefore, they began crafting marionettes.

Tica: They did so not only to commemorate this event but also so that their own deceased relative would have a place to rest their souls.
For hundreds of years, the marionette religion lived on...
Tica: Performance marionettes that can sing, weird songs...
Tica: Could it be that she is the reason behind the marionettes attacking people?
Tica: Hoho~ I'll know the truth once I find you!

Model.Text: Hmph! Behold my power!
Atlas Marionette Workshop VI, hehe~ I smell an important clue hiding inside!
Yikes... this silence is getting on my nerves. As I expected, this workshop is creepy, just like every other workshop.
Ooh, more documents. Lemme take a look...

In addition to crafting marionettes that commemorate deceased relatives, 

our workshop also crafts performance marionettes that operate via runes carved into them...
These are design blueprints for the performance marionettes. Let's see...
So the ones with runes carved into them are for performance purposes, while the ones that don't have runes are to commemorate family members.

Huh? How strange; according to the blueprints, the performance marionettes can only act out simple commands like singing or dancing.
Doesn't say anything about attacking people though?
So the dolls' weird movement...can safely say it has something to do with the singing and that weird runic glow?
T-That's really frightening...

Hmm, what is that?
Origin of the Atlas Marionette Religion, Volume 1...
The wandering boy Karl came across a performance marionette.
Whenever Karl felt depressed and tired from wandering the streets, the marionette would sing a beautiful song to comfort Karl.
Karl's mother often sang him the same song when she was still alive. Thus, Karl always said to others that...
...the marionette contains his mother's soul.
OUCH!
T-They're here as well!?
Now that you've learned your lesson; don't you dare sneak up behind me again!
Origin of the Atlas Marionette Religion, Volume 2...
...Until the day Karl died, the marionette never stopped singing. Her voice sounded as if she was sobbing.
The people of Atlas believed that the marionette did indeed contain the soul of Karl's mother. Therefore, they began crafting marionettes.

They did so not only to commemorate this event but also so that their own deceased relative would have a place to rest their souls.
For hundreds of years, the marionette religion lived on...
Performance marionettes that can sing, weird songs...
Could it be that she is the reason behind the marionettes attacking people?
Hoho~ I'll know the truth once I find you!
